</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">L₁</span> → <span class=\"fn\">L₂</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra.Hom.instCoeFunForall","kind":"instance","line":86,"name":"LieRinehartAlgebra.Hom.instCoeFunForall","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.lean#L86-L86"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra.Hom.«term_→ₗ⁅_⁆_»\"><span class=\"name\">LieRinehartAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">Hom</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_→ₗ⁅_⁆_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A morphism of Lie-Rinehart algebras, from `(A₁, L₁)` to `(A₂, L₂)`, consists of a pair of maps\n`(σ, F)` where `σ : A₁ → A₂` is a morphism of algebras and `F` is a morphism of Lie algebras, which\nrespect the module structures.\n\nHere we define the type of such morphisms with fixed `σ` (which can be regarded as functions\n`L₁ → L₂`). In the future it may be useful to define the type of such morphisms with fixed `F`\n(which can be regarded as functions `A₁ → A₂`) and the type of all such morphisms (which can be\nregarded as functions `A₁ × L₁ → A₂ × L₂`). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra.Hom.«term_→ₗ⁅_⁆_»","kind":"def","line":83,"name":"LieRinehartAlgebra.Hom.«term_→ₗ⁅_⁆_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.lean#L83-L84"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"