class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieRing\">LieRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">L₁</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">A₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">L₁</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieRingModule\">LieRingModule</a> <span class=\"fn\">L₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">A₁</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieAlgebra\">LieAlgebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">L₁</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieRing\">LieRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">L₂</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">A₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">L₂</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieRingModule\">LieRingModule</a> <span class=\"fn\">L₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">A₂</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieAlgebra\">LieAlgebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">L₂</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_extends\">extends</span> <span class=\"fn\">L₁</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieHom\">→ₗ⁅</a><span class=\"fn\">R</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Lie/Basic.html#LieHom\">⁆</a> <span class=\"fn\">L₂</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max u_8 u_9)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"A morphism of Lie-Rinehart algebras, from `(A₁, L₁)` to `(A₂, L₂)`, consists of a pair of maps\n`(σ, F)` where `σ : A₁ → A₂` is a morphism of algebras and `F` is a morphism of Lie algebras, which\nrespect the module structures.\n\nHere we define the type of such morphisms with fixed `σ` (which can be regarded as functions\n`L₁ → L₂`). In the future it may be useful to define the type of such morphisms with fixed `F`\n(which can be regarded as functions `A₁ → A₂`) and the type of all such morphisms (which can be\nregarded as functions `A₁ × L₁ → A₂ × L₂`). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra.Hom","kind":"structure","line":66,"name":"LieRinehartAlgebra.Hom","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.lean#L66-L79"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra.instDerivation\"><span class=\"name\">LieRinehartAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">instDerivation</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A₁</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">A₁</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">A₁</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra\">LieRinehartAlgebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">A₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Derivation/Basic.html#Derivation\">Derivation</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">A₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">A₁</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The derivations of a commutative Algebra themselves form a LieRinehart-Algebra. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra.instDerivation","kind":"instance","line":63,"name":"LieRinehartAlgebra.instDerivation","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.lean#L63-L64"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/LieRinehartAlgebra/Defs.html#LieRinehartAlgebra.instLieRinehartRingDerivation\"><span class=\"name\">LieRinehartAlgebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">instLieRinehartRingDerivation</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span cl